# Quality Gates

- Run type-check and lint before committing.
- Fix test failures -- do not bypass, skip, or suppress them.
- All .skip additions to tests require a comment documenting root cause.

# Code Review

- Use an automated code review tool on every project.
- Before every commit, review staged changes. Apply all suggestions unless they introduce a regression or conflict with project architecture.
- When the tool reviews a PR, address all findings before merging.

# Git Discipline

- Never use --no-verify on git commit or push.
- Never amend published commits without explicit approval.
- Never force-push to main or master without explicit approval.

# Repository Hygiene

- Every project must have a .gitignore. At minimum: node_modules/, dist/, .env*, *.log, OS files.
- Never create orphan files. Every file must be referenced by at least one other file.
- Never commit files over 5MB.
